        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 4:49PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 449 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles east of Veedersburg, or 12 miles northwest of Crawfordsville,
moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hillsboro, New Richmond, Wingate, and Mellott.

This includes Interstate 74 between mile markers 19 and 25.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
